        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 3:50PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 350 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cluster Springs, or near Turbeville, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, heavy rain, and frequent
lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small trees and blow around
unsecured objects. Wind impacting handling of high profile
vehicles. Reduced visibility and minor flooding possible.
Frequent cloud to ground lightning strikes.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of Mecklenburg and
western Lunenburg Counties, including the following locations...
Nelson, Spanish Grove, Arvins Store, Finchley, Finneywood, Skipwith,
Fairview, Plantersville, Rogers Corner, and Blevins Corner.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
